261
00:14:25,336 --> 00:14:26,836
Why would someone like him come here?

262
00:14:27,766 --> 00:14:28,806
Darn it.

263
00:14:29,576 --> 00:14:30,806
There are a lot of strong participants.

264
00:14:31,946 --> 00:14:33,876
One, two... Two more left.

265
00:14:36,546 --> 00:14:37,715
(Seven-star Chef)

266
00:14:37,716 --> 00:14:38,946
"Seven-star Chef."

267
00:14:39,446 --> 00:14:40,446
What?

268
00:14:40,616 --> 00:14:41,886
What do they mean by seven-star?

269
00:14:42,356 --> 00:14:43,656
How did they get seven stars?

270
00:14:44,316 --> 00:14:45,755
(Seven-star Chef)

271
00:14:45,756 --> 00:14:46,786
Don't tell me...

272
00:14:47,226 --> 00:14:49,556
It is him.

273
00:14:50,096 --> 00:14:52,196
Head chef of the hotel in Dubai.

274
00:14:52,796 --> 00:14:54,066
Seven-star Chef.

275
00:14:55,536 --> 00:14:56,635
(Brand Predator)

276
00:14:56,636 --> 00:14:58,566
This is crazy. Really?

277
00:14:59,006 --> 00:15:00,206
Edward Kwon.

278
00:15:03,776 --> 00:15:07,746
Seeing Chef Edward Kwon was unexpected.

279
00:15:08,246 --> 00:15:11,945
He doesn't suit a competition show like this.

280
00:15:11,946 --> 00:15:13,646
He's like the chef of all chefs.

281
00:15:13,946 --> 00:15:16,515
I nurtured my dream of becoming a chef...

282
00:15:16,516 --> 00:15:18,356
by reading his book in university.

283
00:15:18,786 --> 00:15:21,996
Is he actually here? It feels like a dream.

284
00:15:22,396 --> 00:15:23,456
I was shocked.

285
00:15:24,856 --> 00:15:26,726
Nice to meet you. I'm Edward Kwon.

286
00:15:27,366 --> 00:15:29,296
Actually, a seven-star doesn't exist,

287
00:15:29,596 --> 00:15:34,266
but many say the hotel is on another level,

288
00:15:34,566 --> 00:15:36,206
so they call it a seven-star hotel.

289
00:15:36,276 --> 00:15:38,906
I worked at Dubai's Burj Al Arab...

290
00:15:39,046 --> 00:15:41,106
as the head chef.

291
00:15:41,846 --> 00:15:44,316
If I remember correctly, I was 32.

292
00:15:44,776 --> 00:15:46,986
I was very lucky at a young age.

293
00:15:48,216 --> 00:15:50,655
I thought this was the chance...

294
00:15:50,656 --> 00:15:52,286
to go back to the basics.

295
00:15:52,726 --> 00:15:54,026
I'm here to learn too.

296
00:15:55,026 --> 00:15:56,925
(Seven-star Chef, Edward Kwon)

297
00:15:56,926 --> 00:15:58,366
(Fine dining restaurant, Lab XXIV by KUMUDA)

298
00:15:58,696 --> 00:16:00,026
This is no joke.

299
00:16:00,166 --> 00:16:02,365
Edward Kwon was my ex-judge...

300
00:16:02,366 --> 00:16:03,796
- Exactly.
- in the previous show.

301
00:16:05,066 --> 00:16:07,536
I didn't expect the lineup to be this strong.

302
00:16:08,676 --> 00:16:09,936
There's one person left.

303
00:16:10,436 --> 00:16:12,676
(Chinese Cuisine Master)

304
00:16:13,176 --> 00:16:14,846
The last person...

305
00:16:15,946 --> 00:16:17,746
I hope it isn't who I think it is.

306
00:16:18,516 --> 00:16:21,716
Chinese Cuisine Master can't be...

307
00:16:22,256 --> 00:16:24,516
Someone incredible would come out.

308
00:16:30,513 --> 00:16:31,513
It is him.

309
00:16:33,283 --> 00:16:34,313
Seriously?

310
00:16:35,723 --> 00:16:36,823
No way.

311
00:16:37,223 --> 00:16:38,323
No!

312
00:16:38,623 --> 00:16:40,993
(Kim Hee Eun, Michelin Couple, Lim Ki Hak, French Culinary Master)

313
00:16:41,151 --> 00:16:43,660
It is Lee Yeon Bok.

314
00:16:43,661 --> 00:16:45,261
(Kim Ho Yoon, Brand Predator)

315
00:16:45,961 --> 00:16:48,191
The dignity of Chinese cuisine in Korea.

316
00:16:48,691 --> 00:16:49,931
Lee Yeon Bok.

317
00:16:51,101 --> 00:16:52,431
I'm Chef Lee Yeon Bok.

318
00:16:53,801 --> 00:16:56,141
I cooked Chinese cuisine for 53 years.

319
00:16:56,541 --> 00:16:58,841
It's been a long time...

320
00:16:58,871 --> 00:17:02,040
since I last went on a survival show.

321
00:17:02,041 --> 00:17:05,041
But I heard this was a business showdown.

322
00:17:05,411 --> 00:17:07,311
It sounded so fun,

323
00:17:08,151 --> 00:17:09,451
so I gladly accepted it.

324
00:17:09,981 --> 00:17:11,551
"Lee Yeon Bok is still alive and kicking."

325
00:17:11,751 --> 00:17:14,491
I want to show everyone this.

326
00:17:16,691 --> 00:17:20,131
(Lee Yeon Bok, Chinese Cuisine Master)

327
00:17:21,391 --> 00:17:24,761
The best food businesspeople of each field have gathered...

328
00:17:25,131 --> 00:17:26,501
for the business survival show.

329
00:17:27,201 --> 00:17:29,441
Welcome to...

330
00:17:30,001 --> 00:17:31,070
Street Restaurant Fighter.

331
00:17:31,071 --> 00:17:33,411
(Street Restaurant Fighter)

332
00:17:33,571 --> 00:17:35,111
This is insane.

333
00:17:35,841 --> 00:17:36,881
The lineup is too strong.

334
00:17:38,011 --> 00:17:39,581
This won't be easy.

335
00:17:40,481 --> 00:17:41,511
This is bad.

336
00:17:42,751 --> 00:17:43,951
Amazing.

337
00:17:53,361 --> 00:17:54,931
From now on,

338
00:17:55,461 --> 00:17:58,261
you will go to various commercial districts in Korea...

339
00:17:58,931 --> 00:18:01,031
for business showdowns.

340
00:18:02,371 --> 00:18:03,970
Your judges...

341
00:18:03,971 --> 00:18:08,910
(Your judges...)

342
00:18:08,911 --> 00:18:09,981
are the customers.

343
00:18:13,411 --> 00:18:14,781
That's even better.

344
00:18:15,511 --> 00:18:17,181
So it's real business.

345
00:18:17,821 --> 00:18:19,651
Yes, being judged by the customers.

346
00:18:20,451 --> 00:18:21,621
That's the scariest.

347
00:18:23,091 --> 00:18:24,121
They're the scariest.

348
00:18:25,761 --> 00:18:27,831
The winner will be decided by the sales.

349
00:18:28,561 --> 00:18:30,501
Various factors will be reflected,

350
00:18:30,631 --> 00:18:32,461
such as the ingredient cost and customer ratings.

351
00:18:33,871 --> 00:18:35,131
The winner's prize money...

352
00:18:36,241 --> 00:18:37,470
is infinite.

353
00:18:37,471 --> 00:18:38,471
- What?
- What?

354
00:18:39,041 --> 00:18:40,271
Infinite?

355
00:18:40,711 --> 00:18:43,211
What do they mean by infinite?

356
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:47,951
The last person standing on Street Restaurant Fighter...

357
00:18:48,781 --> 00:18:50,321
will win the base prize of 100,000 dollars...

358
00:18:51,121 --> 00:18:52,181
and...

359
00:18:52,451 --> 00:18:56,360
the full amount of the revenue earned on the show.

360
00:18:56,361 --> 00:18:59,461
(You'll get full amount of the revenue earned on the show.)

361
00:18:59,861 --> 00:19:01,831
They take everyone's revenue?

362
00:19:02,691 --> 00:19:04,560
If you get eliminated, you leave your revenue behind?

363
00:19:04,561 --> 00:19:05,631
I guess so.

364
00:19:05,831 --> 00:19:08,301
You can't overlook the average order value.

365
00:19:09,171 --> 00:19:10,801
You need to manage the costs right.

366
00:19:12,041 --> 00:19:13,511
This changes things.

367
00:19:15,041 --> 00:19:17,411
The first task you'll do...

368
00:19:19,181 --> 00:19:21,411
is launching a new brand.

369
00:19:22,551 --> 00:19:23,781
Launch a new brand?

370
00:19:25,821 --> 00:19:27,921
Throw away the name you've been using.

371
00:19:28,521 --> 00:19:32,420
The new signboard will become your name.

372
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:33,460
(Gyeongsang Province Business Monster)

373
00:19:33,461 --> 00:19:34,461
(Brand Predator, Seochon's Icon)

374
00:19:34,791 --> 00:19:36,330
I opened my brand four days ago.

375
00:19:36,331 --> 00:19:38,661
(Kim Ho Yoon, Brand Predator)

376
00:19:38,831 --> 00:19:39,870
You're confident.

377
00:19:39,871 --> 00:19:42,501
That's practically what I do every day.

378
00:19:42,871 --> 00:19:44,301
It's what I do all the time.

379
00:19:45,001 --> 00:19:46,211
Let's just do as usual.

380
00:19:46,611 --> 00:19:48,340
There's the energy you get...

381
00:19:48,341 --> 00:19:51,311
when you first open a restaurant, the resolution to make it work.

382
00:19:51,681 --> 00:19:54,681
You get very excited and nervous.

383
00:19:54,751 --> 00:19:57,751
And when you succeed, you get the thrill.

384
00:19:59,651 --> 00:20:01,421
The street restaurant...

385
00:20:02,021 --> 00:20:04,191
will be revealed right now.

386
00:20:05,591 --> 00:20:06,661
It will be revealed right now.

387
00:20:08,591 --> 00:20:10,531
- Right now?
- With no delay?

388
00:20:11,261 --> 00:20:13,301
(Michelin Couple, French Culinary Master)

389
00:20:16,341 --> 00:20:17,341
I...

390
00:20:17,371 --> 00:20:18,771
Gosh, what's this?

391
00:20:19,841 --> 00:20:22,041
- Oh, my.
- Goodness.

392
00:20:24,341 --> 00:20:25,481
It's going up.

393
00:20:27,211 --> 00:20:28,411
It opens.

394
00:20:29,581 --> 00:20:31,221
This is our restaurant?

395
00:20:32,621 --> 00:20:33,791
Amazing.

396
00:20:34,421 --> 00:20:36,790
- I didn't expect this kind of vibe.
- It's a booth.

397
00:20:36,791 --> 00:20:38,261
They really made it like a restaurant.

398
00:20:38,421 --> 00:20:40,031
This must be the restaurant.

399
00:20:40,561 --> 00:20:42,561
It looked like there were 20 restaurants.

400
00:20:44,131 --> 00:20:46,331
All of these shops will do business at the same time?

401
00:20:53,311 --> 00:20:54,811
- I'm excited.
- I can't wait.

402
00:20:55,411 --> 00:20:56,481
Get a grip.

403
00:20:57,641 --> 00:20:59,311
From the name of the brand...

404
00:20:59,911 --> 00:21:03,221
to the signboard, the interior design, and the menu.

405
00:21:04,081 --> 00:21:06,791
Plan it with your own hands.

406
00:21:07,221 --> 00:21:09,121
Make your own brand...

407
00:21:09,891 --> 00:21:12,461
and sell the food here?

408
00:21:13,131 --> 00:21:15,031
I need to renovate this?

409
00:21:15,391 --> 00:21:18,131
Put up the signboard and everything.

410
00:21:20,031 --> 00:21:21,101
It's big enough to do everything.

411
00:21:22,001 --> 00:21:23,341
I could even butcher a cow here. This is fine.

412
00:21:24,441 --> 00:21:26,041
It's my new restaurant.

413
00:21:30,141 --> 00:21:34,481
(Street Restaurants revealed)

414
00:21:35,811 --> 00:21:37,780
- They have all the basic stuff.
- This...

415
00:21:37,781 --> 00:21:39,280
(Street Restaurant provides only the discussed basic equipment.)

416
00:21:39,281 --> 00:21:40,691
Long time no see.

417
00:21:41,121 --> 00:21:42,350
(Chinese wok range)

418
00:21:42,351 --> 00:21:43,961
This is nice.

419
00:21:44,921 --> 00:21:46,191
The gas stoves.

420
00:21:46,391 --> 00:21:47,861
Three, okay.

421
00:21:48,491 --> 00:21:49,700
This is pretty good.

422
00:21:49,701 --> 00:21:51,031
(Multi-fuel range)

423
00:21:51,931 --> 00:21:53,231
I'll change this...

424
00:21:54,131 --> 00:21:55,731
and put a countertop.

425
00:21:56,201 --> 00:21:57,741
Place a deep fryer and a fridge.

426
00:21:58,741 --> 00:22:00,671
My brain in my head...

427
00:22:01,141 --> 00:22:02,541
kept running.

428
00:22:03,241 --> 00:22:04,941
"Right, I was this excited and had so much fun..."

429
00:22:05,041 --> 00:22:07,211
"when I first created Dookki."

430
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:08,610
I'm so excited.

431
00:22:08,611 --> 00:22:10,481
I'd have so much fun.

432
00:22:11,521 --> 00:22:13,491
Street Restaurant Fighter.

433
00:22:14,251 --> 00:22:17,320
I'll reveal the first mission.

434
00:22:17,321 --> 00:22:18,820
(I'll reveal the first mission.)

435
00:22:18,821 --> 00:22:21,361
- Already.
- Finally revealing the mission.

436
00:22:23,461 --> 00:22:24,531
My heart is racing.

437
00:22:26,161 --> 00:22:27,270
Round One...

438
00:22:27,271 --> 00:22:29,601
(Round One...)

439
00:22:30,501 --> 00:22:32,641
is a 1,000 dollar sales race.

440
00:22:32,971 --> 00:22:33,971
What?

441
00:22:34,111 --> 00:22:35,271
Sales race?

442
00:22:35,811 --> 00:22:37,711
A 1,000 dollar sales race.

443
00:22:38,011 --> 00:22:39,881
You need to hit 1,000 dollars as fast as you can?

444
00:22:40,581 --> 00:22:42,951
If you achieve the 1,000 dollar sales first,

445
00:22:43,421 --> 00:22:45,521
you automatically advance to the next round.

446
00:22:49,221 --> 00:22:51,661
It's all about average order value, really.

447
00:22:52,521 --> 00:22:55,591
You're given 300 dollars for the ingredients.

448
00:22:56,461 --> 00:22:59,061
Make 1,000 dollars out of 300 dollars?

449
00:22:59,831 --> 00:23:01,201
With 300 dollars? How?

450
00:23:01,771 --> 00:23:04,871
When I heard I needed to do business with 300 dollars,

451
00:23:05,401 --> 00:23:08,441
I thought, "What can I buy and what can I sell?"

452
00:23:09,171 --> 00:23:11,110
That 300 dollars weighed on my mind.

453
00:23:11,111 --> 00:23:12,880
What kind of menus...

454
00:23:12,881 --> 00:23:14,281
can I come up with?

455
00:23:14,351 --> 00:23:16,681
If you spend more than 300 dollars on your ingredients,

456
00:23:17,321 --> 00:23:19,850
your sales will start from a negative amount...

457
00:23:19,851 --> 00:23:21,321
which corresponds to the excessive amount you've spent.

458
00:23:23,561 --> 00:23:26,120
(A 1,000 dollar sales race ingredient cost)

459
00:23:26,121 --> 00:23:27,990
(Ingredient cost, 300 dollars, starting sales, 0 dollars)

460
00:23:27,991 --> 00:23:29,030
(Ingredient cost, 470 dollars, starting sales, minus 170 dollars)

461
00:23:29,031 --> 00:23:30,860
Even if you don't spend over 300 dollars,

462
00:23:30,861 --> 00:23:33,131
the leftover cost will vanish.

463
00:23:33,731 --> 00:23:37,170
The sales race is first-come, first-served survival basis.

464
00:23:37,171 --> 00:23:38,570
(They survive based on the order of reaching the goal.)

465
00:23:38,571 --> 00:23:40,270
The business will run for one full day.

466
00:23:40,271 --> 00:23:43,140
After the lunch business, there will be a break...

467
00:23:43,141 --> 00:23:44,710
before the dinner business.

468
00:23:44,711 --> 00:23:45,910
(If they fail to hit the target during the lunch business,)

469
00:23:45,911 --> 00:23:47,081
(they'll continue with the dinner business.)

470
00:23:47,211 --> 00:23:48,710
It's the same.

471
00:23:48,711 --> 00:23:50,481
It's the same as running an actual restaurant.

472
00:23:50,681 --> 00:23:52,520
The two with the lowest sales...

473
00:23:52,521 --> 00:23:54,221
in Round One...

474
00:23:54,651 --> 00:23:55,721
will be eliminated.

475
00:23:55,821 --> 00:23:58,290
They'll shut down the business immediately.

476
00:23:58,291 --> 00:24:00,030
(The two with the lowest sales will shut down their business.)

477
00:24:00,031 --> 00:24:01,491
Eliminated as soon as they start?

478
00:24:01,791 --> 00:24:03,031
That's harsh.

479
00:24:03,531 --> 00:24:04,601
Shut down.

480
00:24:05,761 --> 00:24:07,371
"Shut down." That's so scary.

481
00:24:07,931 --> 00:24:09,771
And this business...

482
00:24:12,141 --> 00:24:14,041
is a blind business.

483
00:24:14,671 --> 00:24:16,071
Blind?

484
00:24:17,441 --> 00:24:19,780
Your faces won't be revealed...

485
00:24:19,781 --> 00:24:21,511
to the customers.

486
00:24:22,911 --> 00:24:24,150
Yes, that's how it should be.

487
00:24:24,151 --> 00:24:26,051
- They should.
- They should be for this.

488
00:24:26,421 --> 00:24:28,051
There are a lot of famous people here.

489
00:24:29,821 --> 00:24:31,461
I cheered internally.

490
00:24:31,861 --> 00:24:34,331
It's worth a shot. I could do it if I worked hard.

491
00:24:34,431 --> 00:24:36,161
That's exactly what people like us wanted.

492
00:24:37,261 --> 00:24:38,831
- Those who aren't known to public.
- It's worth a shot.

493
00:24:39,031 --> 00:24:40,171
A new face.

494
00:24:41,771 --> 00:24:43,271
A new face which the people want.

495
00:24:44,241 --> 00:24:46,271
(Laughing)

496
00:24:46,871 --> 00:24:50,240
Where and how many customers are have become very important now.

497
00:24:50,241 --> 00:24:51,380
- That's right.
- Right.

498
00:24:51,381 --> 00:24:52,911
I'm more curious about the location.

499
00:24:53,981 --> 00:24:55,211
Now,

500
00:24:55,911 --> 00:24:59,621
I'll announce the commercial district of the race.

501
00:24:59,651 --> 00:25:00,721
Where is it?

502
00:25:01,651 --> 00:25:03,721
Where is it? A popular spot?

503
00:25:06,661 --> 00:25:07,761
What's that?

504
00:25:07,831 --> 00:25:08,861
The commercial district?

505
00:25:14,501 --> 00:25:15,571
From the above?

506
00:25:16,841 --> 00:25:18,271
- Where is this?
- Oh, this.

507
00:25:19,201 --> 00:25:20,240
Where is it?

508
00:25:20,241 --> 00:25:21,541
- Where's that?
- Where is it?

509
00:25:21,711 --> 00:25:23,311
- Where is it?
- "Ministry of Education?"

510
00:25:24,341 --> 00:25:26,610
"Ministry of Culture, Sports and Tourism, National Library."

511
00:25:26,611 --> 00:25:27,650
"Ministry of Patriots and Veterans Affairs."

512
00:25:27,651 --> 00:25:29,580
- "Government Complex." - "Government Complex."

513
00:25:29,581 --> 00:25:31,451
- "Government Complex." - It's near that area.

514
00:25:32,851 --> 00:25:35,191
Gwacheon or... Oh, Sejong.

515
00:25:35,551 --> 00:25:37,791
- Isn't it Sejong?
- Is it Sejong-si?

516
00:25:38,291 --> 00:25:40,061
- I think it's Sejong.
- It's Sejong.

517
00:25:41,231 --> 00:25:42,661
Where the government agencies are gathered.

518
00:25:43,091 --> 00:25:44,701
The customers are mainly public officials.

519
00:25:45,101 --> 00:25:49,100
About 12,000 public officials work in this area.

520
00:25:49,101 --> 00:25:50,571
It's a commercial district for office workers.

521
00:25:52,341 --> 00:25:53,471
Okay.

522
00:25:54,541 --> 00:25:56,240
The most important thing about that commercial district...

523
00:25:56,241 --> 00:25:57,940
is that it shouldn't be expensive.

524
00:25:57,941 --> 00:25:59,081
The food needs to be filling.

525
00:25:59,181 --> 00:26:00,910
They have limited time...

526
00:26:00,911 --> 00:26:03,050
to eat.

527
00:26:03,051 --> 00:26:05,350
They need to be able...

528
00:26:05,351 --> 00:26:08,420
to finish their lunch and grab a coffee...

529
00:26:08,421 --> 00:26:09,691
within that one hour.

530
00:26:09,961 --> 00:26:11,391
The estimated number of customers...

531
00:26:11,561 --> 00:26:14,230
is 1,000 for lunch and dinner combined.

532
00:26:14,231 --> 00:26:16,161
(Estimated number: 1,000 customers for lunch and dinner combined)

